OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FLegally they had to stay six feet
OL,7,Fapart. But five years ago Sir Keir
OL,8,FStarmer and Anas Sarwar couldn't have
OL,9,Fbeen much closer politically as they
OL,10,Fgathered during the pandemic in a back
OL,11,Froom at Glasgow Airport.
OL,13,FThe conversation included some blunt
OL,14,Fadvice for the man already eyeing up
OL,15,Fhis road to Downing Street.
OL,17,F"He does and always has struggled with
OL,18,FScotland because it's just not part of
OL,19,Fhis family story," said one of those
OL,20,Fpresent.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,F"We told him, 'You need to learn this
OL,7,Fstuff because it's your job'. He took
OL,8,Fthat really well and because he's a KC
OL,9,Fhe read pages and pages and pages of
OL,10,Fbriefings. Then we would drill him on
OL,11,FScotland and he got it pretty well."
OL,13,FThe partnership took Labour from near-
OL,14,Firrelevance and just a single MP in
OL,15,FScotland into government with a
OL,16,Fmassive majority, including 37
OL,17,Frepresentatives from north of the
OL,18,Fborder.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FAs one loyalist to the end put it:
OL,7,F"When he took over people were saying
OL,8,Fyou just have to ignore Scotland,
OL,9,Fthere's no way you can win there. He
OL,10,Fdidn't believe that and he set about
OL,11,Ftrying to fix that (attitude)."
OL,13,FSir Keir has now stepped down ` to be
OL,14,Freplaced by Andy Burnham ` a mere five
OL,15,Fmonths after Mr Sarwar called for that
OL,16,Foutcome as his own hopes of winning
OL,17,Fpower and becoming first minister
OL,18,Fslipped away.
OL,26,@sD@TpmsD@]pn
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FIt was, as one senior Scottish Labour
OL,7,Ffigure put it, "a real lost
OL,8,Fopportunity".
OL,10,FSo how did it all go so wrong, so
OL,11,Fquickly?
OL,13,F"One of the things we learned in the
OL,14,FScottish election is how much vibes
OL,15,Fmatter," said a senior Labour source.
OL,17,F"Keir is dutiful, hard working and a
OL,18,Fdedicated public servant but that's
OL,19,Fnot the same as vibes. It's not a
OL,20,Fvalue or moral judgment, just a matter
OL,21,Fof politics changing."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FThere was unanimity amongst the dozen
OL,7,Fpeople spoken with for this article
OL,8,Fthat Sir Keir got the "vibes" wrong
OL,9,Ffrom almost the moment he entered
OL,10,FDowning Street.
OL,12,FHe took on the premiership with a
OL,13,Fgloomy outlook that turned off
OL,14,Ffloating voters who had put him into
OL,15,Fpower hoping for a rapid improvement
OL,16,Fin their lives.
OL,18,FEarly on it was announced that winter
OL,19,Ffuel payments would be stripped from
OL,20,Fmillions of pensioners to save money,
OL,21,Fa decision that was later U-turned on.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FThere were also controversies about
OL,7,Fgifts for senior ministers, new
OL,8,Finheritance tax rules for farmers, and
OL,9,Flatterly Lord Mandelson's appointment
OL,10,Fas US ambassador.
OL,12,FBut a separate Scottish Labour source
OL,13,Fargued it was the tone ` or vibes `
OL,14,Fthat made much more of an impact with
OL,15,Fthe public than the controversies.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,F"The thing that killed him and tilted
OL,7,Fthe country against him was to have
OL,8,Frun a campaign saying we are going to
OL,9,Fchange the country and then the first
OL,10,Fthing you say is that things are going
OL,11,Fto get worse," the source said.
OL,13,F"After that everyone's reaction to him
OL,14,Fwas, 'Aha! It's the lying b******'. I
OL,15,Fthink that decision is the single most
OL,16,Fdamaging moment for a UK Government in
OL,17,Fthe last 50 years. No politician has
OL,18,Fexpended so much political goodwill so
OL,19,Fquickly."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FAnother senior Scottish Labour figure
OL,7,Fadded: "Nobody could understand why it
OL,8,Fwas done. It was just bad politics. He
OL,9,Flost trust so quickly."
OL,11,FBut is failure a fair assessment of
OL,12,Fhis legacy as both prime minister and
OL,13,FLabour leader?
OL,15,FScottish Secretary Douglas Alexander
OL,16,Fdoesn't think so.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FHe said: "I nominated Keir in my CLP
OL,7,F(Constituency Labour Party) and I
OL,8,Fvoted for Keir (to be Labour leader)
OL,9,Fbut if you had told me at that time he
OL,10,Fwould manage what Neil Kinnock, John
OL,11,FSmith and Tony Blair took 14 years to
OL,12,Fdo in just one term I would have hoped
OL,13,Fyou were right but probably stepped
OL,14,Facross the road.
OL,16,F"The same as if at any point someone
OL,17,Fhad told me in 2019 we would elect 37
OL,18,FScottish Labour MPs at the next
OL,19,Fgeneral election. Many, many people in
OL,20,FScotland forget how difficult the
OL,21,Fposition had been for many, many years.
OL,26,@oD@ApmoD@[pnpD@PpmpD@dpn
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,F"Literally the electoral achievement
OL,7,Falone puts him in a pantheon of Labour
OL,8,Fleaders. But the best test of any
OL,9,Fprime minister is do you leave the
OL,10,Fcountry in better shape than you found
OL,11,Fit? And I would say the answer to that
OL,12,Fis yes."
OL,14,FIt is true that in 2020, Sir Keir
OL,15,Finherited a Labour Party that had not
OL,16,Flong ago suffered its worst general
OL,17,Felection result since 1935 and was at
OL,18,Fa perilously low ebb in Scotland.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FHe was central, alongside the GMB
OL,7,Ftrade union, in forcing out then
OL,8,FScottish leader Richard Leonard, who
OL,9,Fwas replaced by Mr Sarwar.
OL,11,FFortunes improved, although the party
OL,12,Fwas undoubtedly helped by the collapse
OL,13,Fand rotating leadership of the
OL,14,FConservatives.
OL,16,FThere is personal warmth from some MPs
OL,17,Ftoo. Energy Minister Martin McCluskey
OL,18,Ftold Representing Border that "those
OL,19,Fof us who were elected in 2024 do owe
OL,20,Fa great deal to Keir Starmer".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FEvery person spoken with for this
OL,7,Farticle also highlighted similar areas
OL,8,Fwhen asked about Sir Keir's policy
OL,9,Fachievements.
OL,11,FIncreased public spending, growth
OL,12,F(albeit modest) in the economy,
OL,13,Flifting the two-child limit on
OL,14,Fbenefits, his performance on the world
OL,15,Fstage particularly through a closer
OL,16,Frelationship with the European Union,
OL,17,Fand the awarding of armed forces
OL,18,Fcontracts to Scottish firms came up in
OL,19,Falmost every conversation.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G12/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FScottish Labour's deputy leader Dame
OL,7,FJackie Baillie said: "We are seeing in
OL,8,Freal time defence spending as
OL,9,Finfrastructure investment that will
OL,10,Fturbocharge the economy.
OL,12,F"That's jobs for local people in my
OL,13,Fconstituency ` and for people across
OL,14,FScotland ` that are sustainable and
OL,15,Flong term. Keir has been central to
OL,16,Fthat."
OL,18,FOne MP still loyal to the outgoing
OL,19,Fprime minister stated their belief
OL,20,Fthat Sir Keir could have turned things
OL,21,Faround and won the next election.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G13/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,F"I do think there would have been the
OL,7,Fvotes there in Scotland and across the
OL,8,FUK to defeat the prospect of a Reform
OL,9,Fgovernment," they said, adding that by
OL,10,F2029 it will roughly be a "mid-term"
OL,11,Felection for the SNP-led Scottish
OL,12,FGovernment.
OL,14,FWhy, then, couldn't Sir Keir sell what
OL,15,Feven some of his critics saw as
OL,16,Fsuccess and win back the trust of not
OL,17,Fonly the electorate but also his own
OL,18,Fparliamentarians?
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G14/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FThere is again consensus that not
OL,7,Fbeing "political" held him back. As
OL,8,Fone senior Scottish figure said,
OL,9,Fperhaps damning with faint praise:
OL,10,F"He's been a very good CEO."
OL,12,FThe same source highlighted his final
OL,13,Fprime minister's questions performance
OL,14,Fas showing the qualities which made
OL,15,Fsupporters think Sir Keir would be
OL,16,Fgood at the job ` knowledge of his
OL,17,Fbrief, a genuine care about individual
OL,18,Fpeople's lives and a desire to help
OL,19,Fthem ` but it also highlighted what
OL,20,Fhad been missing up until that point.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G15/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,F"Like Ed Miliband or Gordon Brown he
OL,7,Fwas great behind closed doors and then
OL,8,Fas soon as the TV cameras came on or
OL,9,Fhe went into public he was hopeless,"
OL,10,Fthey said.
OL,12,FThe breaking point for many in
OL,13,FScotland was the Holyrood election
OL,14,Fcampaign, especially when it became
OL,15,Fapparent that Labour was not going to
OL,16,Fcome anywhere close to overhauling the
OL,17,FSNP.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G16/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FIn calling for him to quit, Mr Sarwar
OL,7,Fbroke a bond with Sir Keir that was so
OL,8,Fclose the pair used to send gifts to
OL,9,Feach other's children.
OL,11,F"I don't think they will be friends
OL,12,Fagain any time soon," said one source
OL,13,Ffriendly with Sir Keir.
OL,15,FIn the process, Mr Sarwar also gave up
OL,16,Fany real influence over the UK
OL,17,FGovernment in the doomed hope of it
OL,18,Fbuying him a reprieve with a
OL,19,Fdiscontented electorate.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G17/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,F"I chapped thousands of doors and his
OL,7,Fname was on people's lips," said one
OL,8,Fexperienced campaigner.
OL,10,FThere are certainly plenty of people
OL,11,Fin Labour's Holyrood top team who are
OL,12,Fkeen to pin the blame for defeat on
OL,13,FSir Keir.
OL,15,FOne said: "It wasn't the only factor
OL,16,Fbut you can't divorce the political
OL,17,Fcontext from the election you're
OL,18,Ftaking part in and people were not
OL,19,Fhappy with Keir and the UK Labour
OL,20,Fgovernment."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G18/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32619
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FSome, like the Galloway and West
OL,7,FDumfries candidate Jack McConnel,
OL,8,Fbelieve it is now time for a separate
OL,9,FScottish Labour Party to stop it
OL,10,Fbecoming "extinct by the end of the
OL,11,Fnext decade" as its current
OL,12,Fperformances worsen at every Holyrood
OL,13,Felection.
OL,15,FMr McConnel, who is running the
OL,16,Fcampaign group Just For Scotland,
OL,17,Fsaid: "This isn't about Starmer, or
OL,18,FBurnham, or nationalism. This is about
OL,19,Fwinning. For every moment of inertia,
OL,20,Fwe undermine our movement and our
OL,21,Fvalues."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G19/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32620
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784485125
OL,3,CWhat will be Sir Keir Starmer's legacy
OL,4,Cfor Scotland?
OL,6,FA UK Government source was robust in
OL,7,Fpushing back on that narrative,
OL,8,Fsaying: "Throwing our hands up in the
OL,9,Fair and saying it's too difficult is a
OL,10,Fdereliction of duty.
OL,12,F"In reality, the Scottish Labour Party
OL,13,Fhad total free reign over the Holyrood
OL,14,Fcampaign. There were headwinds from
OL,15,FWestminster but they need to have an
OL,16,Fhonest reflection on what they could
OL,17,Fhave done differently over months and
OL,18,Fyears."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G20/24
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
